\h 3 Yohan
\toc1 3 Yohan (John)
\toc2 3 Yohan
\toc3 3 Yn
\mt2 The third letter
\mt2 that we have written by
\mt1 Yohan (John)
\is1 Introduction
\is2 The author
\ip This the third letter we have that was written by Yohan, one of the twelve apprentices who spent the most time with Yeshua.
\is2 This letter
\ip This letter was sent to one of Yohan's friends named Gaius. Yohan praises Gaius for the way he'd looked after other believers and for his living out God's truth. Yohan also warns Gaius about a person named Diotrephes who was opposing the believers.
\iot Main components of Yohan's letter
\io1 Greetings \ior 1-4\ior*
\io1 Praising Gaius \ior 5-8\ior*
\io1 Scolding Diotrephes \ior 9-10\ior*
\io1 Boasting about Demetrius \ior 11-12\ior*
\io1 The closing \ior 13-15\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\rem /s1 Salutation; Greetings; Trouble in the church
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 1: \xt Acts 19:29; Rom 16:23; 1Cor 1:14.\x*This letter is from Yohan the elderﾂｦ154477 to my dear friend Gaiusﾂｦ154478 who I love \add because we both\add* follow the truthﾂｦ154485.
\rem /s1 Gaius Commended for His Hospitality
\p
\v 2 My dear friend, I trust that you are healthyﾂｦ154493 and doing well in everything just as you are also doing well spiritually.
\v 3 I was very happy when some of our \add spiritual\add* brothersﾂｦ154503 came and told us about yourﾂｦ154507 faithfulness to the truth and how you are living it out.
\v 4 Nothing makes me more happy than hearingﾂｦ154524 that other believers that I've helped are living out the truthﾂｦ154530.
\s1 Praising Gaius
\rem /s1 Caring for the Lord's Workers; Gaius Is Praised
\p
\v 5 My dear friend, you are faithfulﾂｦ154533 in what you doﾂｦ154537 for other believersﾂｦ154541. Even strangersﾂｦ154546
\v 6 have told the assemblyﾂｦ154553 about yourﾂｦ154549 caring for them beforeﾂｦ154552 sending them on. Yourﾂｦ154549 actions will be praised by \nd Godﾂｦ154563\nd*
\v 7 becauseﾂｦ154565 theyﾂｦ154570 wentﾂｦ154570 out to serve God, not getting any help from the unbelievers.
\v 8 We should be supportingﾂｦ154580 believers like them so that we may also becomeﾂｦ154586 their workmates in sharing the truthﾂｦ154590.
\s1 Diotrephes and Demetrius
\p
\v 9 I wroteﾂｦ154591 somethingﾂｦ154593 to the assemblyﾂｦ154595, but Diotrephesﾂｦ154600 won'tﾂｦ154601 listen to us窶派e always wants the limelight for himself.
\v 10 Becauseﾂｦ154604 of that, if I do end up coming, I will be remindingﾂｦ154609 him about what he's been doingﾂｦ154614窶排amblingﾂｦ154617 on againstﾂｦ154617 us with evilﾂｦ154616 talks, and then, not beingﾂｦ154622 happy with that, he doesn't accept other believersﾂｦ154629 and expels them from the assemblyﾂｦ154638 then forbidsﾂｦ154634 others from acceptingﾂｦ154627 them either.
\p
\v 11 My dear friend, don'tﾂｦ154641 copy the evil things \add that others do\add*, just the good things. Anyone who does what is good belongs to God窶蚤nyone who does evil things has not seenﾂｦ154658 God.
\p
\v 12 Demetriusﾂｦ154661 has been talked about by everyone and even the truthﾂｦ154672 itselfﾂｦ154667 speaks. We have also spoken about him, and youﾂｦ154679 know that what weﾂｦ154674 say is true.
\s1 Closing
\rem /s1 Conclusion; Final Greetings
\p
\v 13 I had many things I wanted to writeﾂｦ154692 about, butﾂｦ154694 won'tﾂｦ154695 do it by means of inkﾂｦ154699 andﾂｦ154700 penﾂｦ154701,
\v 14 butﾂｦ154707 instead I hope to seeﾂｦ154711 youﾂｦ154710 soon andﾂｦ154712 then weﾂｦ154717 can speakﾂｦ154717 face to face.
\p
\v 15 Wishing all peace and happiness for you. \add Your\add* friends here also greet you. Please greet \add our\add* friends there by name.
